         <abstract id="aspace_419a2380ff321e86c3193a61826dba70">This collection is made up of the papers of Walter W. Norton and of his wife, Lillian Frances Reynolds Norton. Her papers reflect her work as chairwoman of the Liberty Loan Committee of Lakeville, Connecticut from 1917-1919 and contain correspondence, memoranda, printed matter, receipts, and other material from the various branches of the Committee. Walter W. Norton's papers consist of a bound manuscript genealogical record of the descendants of John Norton and Jane Cooper and letters (1910s-1920s) concerning his stamp collection.</abstract>
